<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="332" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">ambassador of the United States
                                    of America in Rome</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">minister of
                                    foreign affairs of Italy</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-30"><hi rend="italic">March 30,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Your Excellency</hi>:</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to refer to my note of the 1st of March, addressed to
                            your excellency, and to enclose herewith, in confirmation of the
                            information, which I then had the pleasure of transmitting, a copy of
                            the note which I have received from the Department of State, announcing
                            the acceptance by the President of the United States of the joint
                            invitation of the Governments of Italy and Colombia to arbitrate between
                            them in regard to the claims of one Ernest Cerruti.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wayne MacVeagh.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>